Release_description: Trade Logistics Information Pipeline TLIP release_ver_1.2.2_QA_Environment_20251111 DSL No#15756
Functionality_delivered: 1. Overview This release fixes a critical data extraction issue where XML documents with leading whitespace were incorrectly detected as text/plain instead of application/xml, causing document data extraction to fail and return empty properties. Major highlights: {U+2022}Enhanced MIME type detection to handle XML documents with leading whitespace {U+2022}Improved robustness of data extraction for export declaration documents 2. API Changes No API changes in this release. 3. Architecture Changes 3.1 Schema Updates No schema updates in this release. 3.2 Configurations No configuration changes required. 3.3 ADRs No new ADRs in this release. 4. Communication Flows No changes to communication flows in this release. 5. Troubleshooting Issue: Export declaration documents returning empty properties { properties: [], identifiers: [], events: [] } Root Cause: XML documents with leading whitespace were detected as text/plain instead of application/xml. Resolution: Upgrade to version 1.2.2 - MIME type detection now trims leading whitespace before checking XML content. If previously failing documents still don't extract after upgrade: 1.Verify the service has been restarted to pick up the new build 2.Check that detectedFileMimeType in logs shows application/xml instead of text/plain 3.Ensure the document starts with <message> or <?xml (after trimming whitespace) 6. Validation Scenario 1.Submit export declaration XML document with leading space character to the data extraction service 2.Verify MIME type is detected as application/xml in logs 3.Confirm data extraction returns populated properties array with expected fields (e.g. sad_id, consignor, items, etc.) 4.Test with leading space ( ), tab (\t), and newline (\n) characters 5.Verify backward compatibility - standard documents without leading whitespace still extract correctly 7. Review & Approvals Reviewer Role Approval Date Steve Otieno Software Engineer 2025-10-29 8. Change Log Type Description PR/Commit fix Enhanced MIME type detection to trim leading whitespace before XML content check mimeTypeHelper.ts:62-66 fix Resolved export declaration data extraction failures caused by leading whitespace N/A 9. Appendices - Investigation Summary Problem: Export declaration documents failing to extract data, returning empty results. Root Cause Analysis: 1.XML documents in the data pipeline acquired leading whitespace 2.MIME type detection checked only exact match at position 0: "<?xml " or "<message" 3.Documents starting with " <message>" (space before <) failed the check 4.MIME type was incorrectly detected as "text/plain" 5.XML parsing was skipped, causing empty extraction results Solution: Trim leading whitespace before performing XML content detection.

Release_description: Trade Logistics Information Pipeline TLIP release_ver_1.2.3_QA_Environment_20251112 DSL No#15807
Functionality_delivered: 1. Overview This release improves the robustness and error handling of the KRA data provider, specifically for Certificate of Origin (COO) message processing. Major Highlights: {U+2022}Enhanced error handling for Certificate of Origin message processing 2. API Changes No API changes in this release. 3. Architecture Changes 3.1 Schema Updates No schema updates in this release. 3.2 Configurations No configuration changes required. 3.3 ADRs No new ADRs in this release. 4. Communication Flows No changes to communication flows in this release. 5. Troubleshooting Issue: Certificate of Origin message processing fails and causes the entire consumer to crash Root Cause: Unhandled exceptions in handleCooMessage were not caught, causing the message consumer to fail Resolution: Upgrade to version 1.2.3. Error handling is now in place to catch and log COO processing failures without crashing the consumer. 6. Validation Scenario 1.Submit a malformed or invalid Certificate of Origin message to the KRA COO queue 2.Verify that the error is logged with the message: "Failed to process Certificate Of Origin message." 3.Confirm that the consumer continues processing subsequent messages without crashing 4.Verify that the message is acknowledged (ack) even after processing failure 5.Test with valid COO messages to ensure backward compatibility and successful processing 7. Review & Approvals Reviewer Role Approval Date Steve Otieno Software Engineer 2025-11-13 8. Change Log Type Description PR/Commit fix Add error handling for Certificate of Origin message processing KradataProvider.ts 9. Appendices (Workshop Notes / Feedback Summary) Investigation Summary Problem: Certificate of Origin message processing failures were causing the entire consumer to fail, preventing subsequent messages from being processed. Root Cause Analysis: 1.The handleCooMessage method could throw exceptions during processing 2.No try-catch block was in place to handle these exceptions gracefully 3.Unhandled exceptions caused the consumer callback to fail 4.The consumer would stop processing messages until manually restarted Solution: Wrapped the handleCooMessage call in a try-catch block to log errors without disrupting the consumer flow.
